    "title": "Also try Minecraft!",
    "description": "Always incendiary. Fires a 3x3 grid of fireballs that can ricochet and then explode on impact or after bouncing. Most of its output comes from splash damage, and the thrown-weapon reload also benefits strongly from explosive-style scaling."
  },
  "notes": "The 3x3 layout never changes. Extra pellet bonuses from parts, prefixes, or other effects can still raise its damage even when additional projectiles are not obvious on screen. Grenade-damage bonuses increase both the splash from its shots and the damage from its Tediore reload throw, while some effects that expect normal pellet hits may not behave as usual.",
